# Mahesh Bansal

**Born:** 7 January 1975, Muzaffarnagar, Uttar Pradesh, India  
**Nationality:** Indian  
**Party:** Samajwadi Party (1992–present)  
**Profession:** Politician  
**Parents:** SK Bansal (father)  
**Children:** 2

---

## Political Career

- **Minister of State (Nominated) for Economics and Statistics (Planning) Department, Government of Uttar Pradesh**  
  *Term:* 1 April 2016 – 31 March 2017  
  *Chief Minister:* Akhilesh Yadav

- **State Secretary, Samajwadi Party Uttar Pradesh**  
  *Term start:* 1 April 2017  
  *President:* Akhilesh Yadav

Mahesh Bansal is considered close to Mulayam Singh Yadav.

---

## Summary

Mahesh Bansal (born 7 January 1975) is an Indian politician. He was appointed Minister of State (Nominated) for Economics and Statistics (Planning) Department of Uttar Pradesh in the Akhilesh Yadav Ministry from 2016 to 2017. He has been considered close to Mulayam Singh Yadav.

He was appointed State Secretary of Samajwadi Party Uttar Pradesh in 2017 when UP CM Akhilesh Yadav was President of the Samajwadi Party.

